00:01:39,079 --> 00:01:42,650
[Episode Four]

3
00:01:42,674 --> 00:01:47,457
{\an8}[Qianmen Street, Beijing]

4
00:01:55,678 --> 00:01:58,581
{\an8}[Li Dazhao, styled Shou Chang, editor-in-chief of the "Morning Bell"]

5
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,796
Where do you live, brother?

6
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:01,356
Outside Yondingmen, as a pariah.

7
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,876
Why do you say this?

8
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,716
Those who pull carts, wield skill in trade

9
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:07,036
have shaved heads, are pig butchers, coffin carriers,

10
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,076
all live over there.

11
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,956
Then how is getting by in life right now for you guys?

12
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:14,316
Impossible to get by. Everyone's suffering until they can't take it anymore.

13
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:15,516
According to the older generations' saying,

14
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:17,436
we have never gone through such sullen days.

15
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:20,316
Didn't you say that since this President Lai has took office,

16
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,516
he has made a lot of promises?

17
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,876
President Lai!

18
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,716
He only cares about fighting with Duan Qirui for power,

19
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:27,740
he doesn't care about the lives of the people.

20
00:02:33,380 --> 00:02:37,036
Good people, I'm begging you.

21
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:39,036
My child has high fever for days now.

22
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:40,878
I'm begging you.

23
00:02:40,902 --> 00:02:42,556
I'm begging you.

24
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:45,580
People are worse than animals.

25
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:48,956
Brother.

26
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:51,020
Pull over for a moment.

27
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:55,972
Good people, I'm begging you.

28
00:02:55,996 --> 00:02:57,408
I'm begging you.

29
00:02:57,432 --> 00:02:59,746
I'm begging you.

30
00:03:01,712 --> 00:03:04,694
{\an8}[Zhao Shiyan, styled Qin Sheng, student at The High School Affiliated to Beijing Normal University]

31
00:03:04,718 --> 00:03:07,198
I'm begging you.

32
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:12,316
What's wrong with you?

33
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:14,156
What's going on with this guy?

34
00:03:14,180 --> 00:03:15,200
Go!

35
00:03:15,224 --> 00:03:17,343
{\an8}[Ge Shugui, worker at Changxindian, Beijing]

36
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:17,596
This is my daughter-in-law!

37
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:19,996
You can't do that even if she's your daughter-in-law!

38
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:21,196
What are you doing here?

39
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:22,956
What's the point of making a fool of yourself here?

40
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:24,956
Am I ashamed? Ge Shugui!

41
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:27,756
If... if I leave, the child will be dead.

42
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:30,876
We poor people are born to die.

43
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,556
A poor man's life is not a fragile one.

44
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:35,727
You can't die standing up, you know?

45
00:03:35,751 --> 00:03:36,190
Go!

46
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:38,780
You go!

47
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:43,020
I want you to kneel!

48
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,156
I want you to kneel!

49
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,196
Why are you hitting her?

50
00:03:45,220 --> 00:03:45,996
Don't hit her!

51
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:46,716
I want you to kneel!

52
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:47,916
What kind of skill is beating someone up?

53
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:49,196
Yeah!

54
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:50,476
Brother!

55
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,380
Don't fight. Don't fight.

56
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,340
I said stop fighting!

57
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:53,380
Don't fight!

58
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,676


59
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,372
I have money.

60
00:03:54,396 --> 00:03:54,960
I have money.

61
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:55,916
I have money, you can have it.

62
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:58,300
I'll see what I can do, brother.

63
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:00,156
Lend me some money, will you?

64
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,203
Brother, save the child!

65
00:04:01,227 --> 00:04:01,940
Brother, save the child!

66
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:02,876
Why are you still kneeling?

67
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:03,745
Save the child!

68
00:04:03,745 --> 00:04:04,396
Why are you still kneeling?

69
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:05,516
Lend some money, brother.

70
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:06,556
Lend me some money.

71
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:07,676
Sister, sister.

72
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,356
Save the child, save the children.

73
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:10,396
Lend me some money.

74
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:11,980
Sister, sister.

75
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:13,916
Have pity on the child.

76
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,836
Sister-in-law, take the children with you.

77
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,820
I'll take you to the doctor.

78
00:04:18,260 --> 00:04:20,343
Get up.

79
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:23,436
Pull the cart over.

80
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:24,780
Got it!

81
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,556
Go now, go.

82
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:27,885
Mister!

83
00:04:27,909 --> 00:04:30,146
Mister! Thank you!

84
00:04:30,432 --> 00:04:31,300
Mister! Thank you!

85
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,235
Get up! Quickly, get up!

86
00:04:32,259 --> 00:04:33,039
Quickly, get up! Up!

87
00:04:33,063 --> 00:04:34,387
Get up!

88
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:35,916
Student.

89
00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:37,196
Which hospital is closest to here?

90
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:38,199
The French hospital.

91
00:04:38,223 --> 00:04:38,876
The French hospital!

92
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:39,516
Come on, I'll take you there.

93
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:39,916
Alright.

94
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:40,236
Come, come, come.

95
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:42,060
Make way, make way.

96
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,716
Come on, slow down.

97
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,422
Be careful.

98
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:50,503
Go.

99
00:04:51,422 --> 00:04:53,001
Why are you still standing there?

100
00:04:53,025 --> 00:04:55,156
Come on, go!

101
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:57,069
Go!

102
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:01,500
Aiya... I'm so angry!

103
00:05:08,420 --> 00:05:09,916
Your great kindness, mister.

104
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:10,316
Get up.

105
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:11,196
I can't repay you.

106
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,276
If you need me in the future, just ask.

107
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:15,196
You don't have to be so polite.

108
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,796
Let's get to know each other.

109
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:17,996
My name is Li Dazhao.

110
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:19,756
Just arrived in Beijing to run a newspaper.

111
00:05:19,780 --> 00:05:21,676
You are Mr. Li Shou Chang.

112
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:23,036
I have read your book.

113
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,476
I admire you.

114
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:27,436
Student, I admire you too.

115
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:28,476
How do I call you?

116
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,196
My name is Zhao Shiyan.

117
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:31,980
A student at The High School Affiliated to Beijing Normal University.

118
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:34,876
My name is Ge Shugui, a worker from Changxingdian.

119
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,316
What do you do as a worker?

120
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:39,356
Locomotive repair.

121
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:40,556
Good.

122
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,956
I've just arrived in Beijing and I don't know my way around.

123
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:45,100
Let's be friends.

124
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:47,436
I can't afford that.

125
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:49,036
Equality for all.

126
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:51,036
There is no distinction between high and low culture.

127
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,436
Sir, how can I be like you?

128
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:57,180
Look at what you're saying, I can't even answer.

129
00:05:57,380 --> 00:05:59,116
You can't say that.

130
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:01,676
The tough talk on the street just now

131
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,276
had us all in stitches.

132
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:03,756
Right.

133
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,460
Brother Ge is a man with a backbone.

134
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:09,900
It's coming.

135
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:12,780
How's it going?

136
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:16,220
Son.

137
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,156
Doctor.

138
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,316
Doctor, how is my son?

139
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:23,296
Needs hospitalisation.

140
00:06:23,296 --> 00:06:24,236
hospitalisation.

141
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,516
It's so serious!

142
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:28,716
Don't worry, it's not life-threatening.

143
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:32,156
You guys go ahead and check in.

144
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:34,156
How much does it cost to get admitted to hospital.

145
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:37,820
Around thirty dollars or so.

146
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,996
Baby will protect you.

147
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:45,276
Shugui.

148
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,700
Follow me.

149
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:08,979
I cannot accept.

150
00:07:09,003 --> 00:07:10,476
I cannot accept, Mr. Dazhao!

151
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,356
For your willingness to help us,

152
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,956
we are already very grateful.

153
00:07:12,980 --> 00:07:14,716
How can we ask you to sell something?

154
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:16,476
We should do it ourselves!

155
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,956
Do you need to go out on the street if you've got what it takes?

156
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:21,436
Don't worry, these things don't get in the way of life.

157
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:23,180
Come.

158
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:33,436
Short sleeves with missing lapels, few buttons and no buttons,

159
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:35,436
a protective cover each with an open bottom,

160
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:37,916
and a pair of leather shoes.

161
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:40,860
Two silver dollars.

162
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:45,516
No, it won't work!

163
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:47,196
Mr. Dazhao, you can't use this.

164
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:49,660
You can't! You can't!

165
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,420
And this.

166
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:07,036
Worn out, wrong time,

167
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:08,956
one old pocket watch.

168
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:11,916
Four silver dollars in total when sold.

169
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:12,636
Sold.

170
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:15,020
I don't regret doing this.

171
00:08:15,220 --> 00:08:17,356
Short sleeves with missing lapels, few buttons and no buttons,

172
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:18,956
