173
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:22,060
and a pair of leather shoes.

174
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:25,116
Worn out, wrong time,

175
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:26,181
one old pocket watch.

176
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:28,220
I don't regret doing this.

177
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:39,020
Shugui, come with me somewhere.

178
00:08:43,811 --> 00:08:47,534
{\an8}[Editorial board of the "Morning Bell"]

179
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,996
Come on, come on. Higher.

180
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:48,156
Higher, higher. Balance on both sides.

181
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:49,820
Wait for me here.

182
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:50,636
Good. Nailed it.

183
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,540
Lao Xie.

184
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:55,116
Mr. Shou Chang! Welcome, welcome.

185
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:56,236
Just about to go to the station.

186
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,356
No more pleasantries for now.

187
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:59,260
Lend me thirty dollars quickly.

188
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:02,076
I have a friend who has a family emergency.

189
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:02,956
You lend it to me

190
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:05,898
and just take it out of my salary next month.

191
00:09:05,922 --> 00:09:06,636
OK.

192
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:07,436
Xiang Li!

193
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:08,716
Go and get thirty silver dollars.

194
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:09,436
Alright, alright.

195
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:11,180
Hurry up.

196
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:12,796
How's your health?

197
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:13,836
Same as always, OK.

198
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,036
You caught me off guard.

199
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:18,220
You see, the welcome ceremony is being set up for you.

200
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:20,396
Good.

201
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,820
Here.

202
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,100
Shugui.

203
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,580
Thirty dollars.

204
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:34,700
Brother Ge.

205
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:39,820
As you said, poor people don't have a fragile life.

206
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:43,660
Save a life, quickly!

207
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,516
Lao Xie.

208
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:12,300
You'll also have to lend me ten dollars.

209
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:13,996
I need to get my stuff

210
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:15,356
back from the pawnshop.

211
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:16,796
Hurry up, hurry up and get it.

212
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:17,916
Good trip. How are you?

213
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:19,916
Come on, big guy.

214
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:21,116
We warmly welcome

215
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:24,277
editor-in-chief Li Dazhao, who has returned from Japan.

216
00:10:24,301 --> 00:10:25,600
Good!

217
00:10:25,624 --> 00:10:27,097
Good!

218
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:28,716
Hello.

219
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:30,420
Student, take a look and see!

220
00:10:29,298 --> 00:10:33,344
{\an8}[Aurora College, Shanghai]

221
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:32,476
This issue of the "New Youth"

222
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,956
especially "Youth" by Mr. Li Dazhao

223
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:36,076
is the most exciting.

224
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,220
Let me read you a paragraph:

225
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,316
"To advance civilisation for the world,"

226
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,396
"to create happiness for mankind,"

227
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,916
"with our youthful selves,"

228
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:45,996
"to create a youthful family,"

229
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,276
"a youthful nation,"

230
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:49,116
"a youthful people,"

231
00:10:49,140 --> 00:10:51,036
"a youthful humanity,"

232
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:52,636
"a youthful earth,"

233
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:55,340
"a youthful universe..."

234
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,420
Sorry about that!

235
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:05,436
Who's there?

236
00:11:05,460 --> 00:11:07,500
Did you see if there's anyone up here?

237
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:09,580
It's her!

238
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,860
The one with the accordion at the back!

239
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,156
That's me.

240
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:17,436
Did you see anyone down here?

241
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:19,116
What's going on?

242
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:21,756
It's wet. The magazines are wet.

243
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:23,676
I was in a hurry to get to class and didn't see them.

244
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,500
How about this,

245
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:29,756
I'll give you ten dollars.

246
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:31,910
You catch!

247
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:39,196
What an attitude!

248
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:40,396
Who are you shouting at?

249
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:41,676
What's wrong with me yelling at you?

250
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,636
Get down here!

251
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,778
Then you wait there.

252
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:49,260
God there are people like this.

253
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:51,820
Brother, I'm all wet.

254
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:04,780
Who are you shouting at?

255
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:07,276
Do you know what you've done wrong?

256
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,596
Whoever you are, you've drenched the magazine

257
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:12,156
and you haven't even said you're sorry.

258
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:13,676
I've given you the money.

259
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,356
I've just made it very clear.

260
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:17,036
I was in a hurry to get to class, I didn't see it.

261
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:18,716
I was just up there, I couldn't get down.

262
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:19,676
What more do you want from me?

263
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:20,876
Do you give money like that?

264
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:21,996
I don't mean your money.

265
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:23,196
It's as much as it should be.

266
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:24,860
Qiaonian, how many copies?

267
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:25,723
What's your attitude?

268
00:12:25,747 --> 00:12:26,636
What's your attitude?

269
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:27,916
With a woman like you scattering flowers in the sky

270
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:28,556
and throwing money away?

271
00:12:28,580 --> 00:12:29,318
Thirteen copies.

272
00:12:29,342 --> 00:12:30,156
Thirteen copies.

273
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:31,756
Twenty-two cents per copy.

274
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:32,476
How much money?

275
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,356
Two dollars and eighty-six cents.

276
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:35,356
Add to that the word "Sorry".

277
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:36,796
I've given you ten dollars.

278
00:12:36,820 --> 00:12:38,716
You can pay for all your magazines for ten dollars.

279
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:40,636
Ten dollars will get you both a lot of food.

280
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,156
Who wants to go out for dinner on your dime?

281
00:12:42,180 --> 00:12:43,036
Do you have any manners

282
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:44,076
and are you reasonable?

283
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,116
Did your family ever teach you

284
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:46,316
the rules?

285
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:47,116
Rules, huh?

286
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:49,116
Then I'll give you a good lecture on the rules today.

287
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:50,156
This is a school.

288
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:51,436
You have broken a school rule.

289
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,236
The school rule is

290
00:12:52,260 --> 00:12:53,916
that no one is allowed to set up a stall here.

291
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:56,076
You've set up a stall and you're in breach of school rules.

292
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:57,036
I'm still really surprised.

293
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,076
Who are you?

294
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,436
What are you doing?

295
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:01,196
I suddenly remembered that I hadn't met you guys before.

296
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:02,476
Sister, how did you get here?

297
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,756
Sister, we are new students.

298
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:04,716
New students, are you?

299
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:06,956
New students are expected to follow the school rules.

300
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,236
The new students don't study hard,

301
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:10,316
they just set up shop and do business here

302
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:11,596
which will delay their studies.

303
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:13,756
How can you live up to the parents who provide for you?

304
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:15,276
Who doesn't study well anymore?

305
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:17,596
We call this work-study after school.

306
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:20,076
French class is a preparatory class for work-study in France.

307
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,196
Then we can work-study in France

308
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:22,316
but not in our own country.

309
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:23,356
What's the point?

310
00:13:23,380 --> 00:13:24,716
Work-study?

311
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,396
That's a trendy way of putting it.

312
00:13:26,420 --> 00:13:28,316
There are rules everywhere in China.

313
00:13:28,340 --> 00:13:30,156
School rules are school rules.

314
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:31,916
Yes, we are new students

315
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:32,716
and we don't know the rules.

316
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:33,756
But now that we know

317
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:34,396
we can walk

318
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:36,316
but before that happens, you have to say one word to us.

319
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:37,436
"Sorry"

320
00:13:37,460 --> 00:13:39,276
We'll leave as soon as we've finished.

321
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:40,396
I've grown up

322
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:42,476
and never said that word.

323
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:43,276
Are you leaving?

324
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:44,396
I'm not leaving.

325
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:46,060
OK.

326
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,396
Supervisor!

327
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:49,276
Sister, don't!

328
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,236
Don't stop her. Let her shout.

329
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:50,820
Sister, don't shout.

330
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:51,916
Shout!

331
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:52,156
Supervisor!

332
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:53,116
Sister, don't shout.

333
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:53,996
We are not like the others.

334
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:55,540
The "New Youth" magazine is an emancipator of the mind!

335
00:13:54,592 --> 00:13:56,433
{\an8}[Chen Qiaonian, second son of Chen Duxiu]

336
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,036
Do you know Mr. Li Dazhao?

337
00:13:57,060 --> 00:13:58,716
I don't know Li Dazhao.

338
00:13:58,740 --> 00:13:59,526
You leaving?

339
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:00,956
Not leaving.

340
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,636
OK, hold this for me.

341
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:04,556
Don't do this.

342
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:05,916
Not leaving, are you?

343
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:07,900
I'll do it.

344
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:10,556
Sister!

345
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:12,716
What are you doing? You want to go insane?

346
00:14:12,740 --> 00:14:13,836
I didn't ask for trouble.

347
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:14,636
The students are watching

348
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:15,356
while I reasoned with her.

349
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:17,116
I'm not being a jerk.

350
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:18,476
Put the magazines down.

351
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,756
You're a stubborn person.

352
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:20,796
There's no reasoning with you!

353
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:21,836
Why do you have no sense at all?

354
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:23,036
Sister, don't take our things!

355
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,396
Have a good talk!

356
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,380
You give me back the magazine!

357
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:27,756
Sister!

358
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:29,180
Make way!

359
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:38,956
Brother, let's sell it somewhere else.

360
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:40,636
Don't sell it here.

361
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:42,220
Alright.

362
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,580
Sell it there and nowhere else.

363
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:52,556
Here you go.

364
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:54,380
Thank you.

365
00:14:54,820 --> 00:14:55,676
Grandpa,

366
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:56,956
I'll set up a stall here

367
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:59,196
to sell "New Youth" magazines.

368
00:14:59,220 --> 00:14:59,836
What?

369
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,196
I want a stall here selling magazines,

370
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:02,396
is it a concern for you?

371
00:15:02,420 --> 00:15:03,756
Selling books.

372
00:15:03,780 --> 00:15:04,796
What book?

373
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,316
"New Youth"

374
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:07,516
Sell it, sell it.

375
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:09,580
Thank you!

376
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,436
To love or not to love.

377
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:12,796
It's not easy to watch them.

378
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:14,076
They are the ones who work and study.

379
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,756
Let's all disperse and get on with it.

380
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:17,740
Close the door.

381
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:29,756
Take a look and see!

382
00:15:29,780 --> 00:15:31,756
Don't miss it passing by!

383
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:33,756
"New Youth", just published!

384
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:36,156
See Mr. Li Dazhao's "Youth"!

385
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:38,316
See the newly published "New Youth"!

386
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:39,436
Young man, how much is the magazine?

387
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:41,516
Hello, twenty-two cents a copy.

388
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:42,156
Come and have a look.

389
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:43,980
I'll take a look.

390
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,676
Yes, I'll take one.

391
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,420
Twenty-two cents.

392
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:51,907
That's it. Thank you.

393
00:15:51,985 --> 00:15:53,887
Have a good read. Qianian, receipt!

394
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:54,636
OK.

395
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:55,756
"New Youth"!

396
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:56,156
Hello.

397
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:56,716
How much is "New Youth"?

398
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:57,516
Twenty-two cents a copy.

399
00:15:57,540 --> 00:15:58,636
I'll take one.

400
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:00,060
Take a look.

401
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:01,116
That's it. Thank you.

402
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:03,260
Hello, have a look at the "New Youth".

403
00:16:03,380 --> 00:16:04,316
Qiaonian!

404
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:06,060
Two copies!

405
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,316
Come, take a look!

406
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:10,636
See Mr. Li Dazhao's "Youth"!

407
00:16:10,660 --> 00:16:13,420
See the newly published "New Youth"!

408
00:16:13,620 --> 00:16:14,556
Thank you!

409
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:16,620
Brother, I've got one here too.

410
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:18,236
Don't mess it up.

411
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:20,716
"New Youth"!

412
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:22,556
See Mr. Li Dazhao's "Youth"!

413
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:24,140
This is a well written paragraph.

414
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:25,596
Stop, stop, stop.

415
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:26,476
See Mr. Li Dazhao's "Youth"!

416
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:29,340
See the newly published "New Youth"!

417
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,836
Young man.

418
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,116
Let me ask you something.

419
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,396
Do you have

420
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:36,156
the newly reissued issue

421
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:38,076
of the magazine that published

422
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:38,636
Li Dazhao's "Youth"?

423
00:16:38,660 --> 00:16:40,236
Sure thing.

424
00:16:40,260 --> 00:16:40,956
Let me have a look.

425
00:16:40,980 --> 00:16:41,756
Go ahead.

426
00:16:41,780 --> 00:16:43,036
Many people like it. They're buying the magazine

427
00:16:43,060 --> 00:16:44,700
just for that article.

428
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,396
Yes. That's the one.

429
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:49,916
The Master had me looking for it for several days.

430
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:50,876
Finally found it.

431
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,396
I'll buy two issues.

432
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:53,516
Two?

433
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:54,156
How much?

434
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:54,716
Here you go.

435
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:55,916
Forty-four cents all together.

436
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:57,196
Twenty-two cents each.

437
00:16:57,220 --> 00:16:57,756
Alright.

438
00:16:57,780 --> 00:16:59,820
This one is new. Take it.

439
00:17:01,540 --> 00:17:02,556
Here.

440
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:03,916
No problem. It's ok if you don't buy it.

441
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,500
You can read it first.

442
00:17:09,380 --> 00:17:11,756
You can't stop here. Move along.

443
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,276
Right away.

444
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,900
Mister, we have to go.

445
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:17,676
Coming!

446
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:18,316
Here's your change.

447
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:19,116
Here.

448
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:19,996
Thank you!

449
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,420
Take care.

450
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:24,060
Alrighty.

451
00:17:25,060 --> 00:17:26,796
Alright, here you go.

452
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:27,516
Qiaonian,

453
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:28,236
are you keeping track?

454
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:29,596
That's another two issues.

455
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:31,156
Yes.

456
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:33,740
I've got a few too.

457
00:17:34,740 --> 00:17:42,740
{\an8}[Baishun Lane, Qianmenwei Street, Beijing]

458
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:50,796
Brothers,

459
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:53,916
Let's not go to second-rate tea rooms.

460
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:57,196
And let's not go to third-rate lodgings.

461
00:17:57,220 --> 00:18:01,836
But rather to this first-rate sing-song house!

462
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:05,180
Lan Xiang Ban!

463
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:10,020
Gui Jin Luan!

464
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,036
Young Masters, be quiet.

465
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,756
Your brother is here!

466
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:15,340
Young Masters.

467
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:18,316
Master Zhang, to tell you the truth,

468
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:20,156
right now, Gui Jin Luan

469
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:22,396
is entertaining Master Hu from your Peking University.

470
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:26,156
The music is coming from her room.

471
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:27,380
Master Hu?

472
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:29,460
Which Master Hu?

473
00:18:29,460 --> 00:18:31,540
The Master Hu from Peking University, Hu Jun.

474
00:18:31,540 --> 00:18:31,996
That's right.

475
00:18:32,020 --> 00:18:33,996
He's been here for several days.

476
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,836
Hu Jun?

477
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:37,836
I know him!

478
00:18:37,860 --> 00:18:41,420
He got a professorship due to his relative Duan Qirui.

479
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:43,596
Taking money and not teaching properly.

480
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:46,156
Spending all day eating, drinking, and gambling,

481
00:18:46,180 --> 00:18:49,356
his reputation stinks to high heaven.

482
00:18:49,380 --> 00:18:51,356
Since he's been here for a few days,

483
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,356
then ask him to take a break.

484
00:18:53,380 --> 00:18:55,116
Let's give him a hand.

485
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:57,276
Besides, as a teacher,

486
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,820
he ought to defer to students.

487
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:00,796
Get out of the way.

488
00:19:00,820 --> 00:19:08,796
Master Zhang, Master Zhang!

489
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:09,756
What are you doing just standing there?

490
00:19:09,780 --> 00:19:11,276
Hurry up and call the police!

491
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:14,540
Master Zhang!

492
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:17,740
Stop fighting!

493
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:21,900
Help!

494
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:28,666
{\an8}[Shanghai]

495
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:50,940
There's a purse here.

496
00:19:51,620 --> 00:19:52,716
Where did you find it?

497
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:54,540
Inside the book.

498
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,076
Do you have any recollection

499
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,676
of anyone who was here with that purse?

500
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,500
Can't remember.

501
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:05,916
Five hundred and eighty-three silver dollars.

502
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:06,956
So much money.

503
00:20:06,980 --> 00:20:07,596
Five eighty-three!

504
00:20:07,620 --> 00:20:08,716
Quiet!

505
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:10,540
Let me count it.

506
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:14,700
Song Ah Di.

507
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:17,196
There's no address. Only a name.

508
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:20,316
If no one claims it, then we've hit the jackpot.

509
00:20:20,340 --> 00:20:21,756
Hit what jackpot?

510
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,460
If you had lost this money, wouldn't you be worried?

511
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,940
Then how do we give it back?

512
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:30,636
Let's wait.

513
00:20:30,660 --> 00:20:33,100
See if anyone comes to claim it.

514
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:35,260
Clean up.

515
00:21:14,660 --> 00:21:15,676
Not going home?

516
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,476
We'll be going right away.

517
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:17,996
It's getting dark.

518
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:19,516
Should get going.

519
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:19,836
Take care.

520
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:22,140
See you tomorrow.

521
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,380
Friends, friends.

522
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:43,996
Have a drink. No, no.

523
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:46,156
Why not?

524
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:49,820
Just sit there, then.

525
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:03,300
Brother.

526
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:04,636
Hungry.

527
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:06,356
Bear with it.

528
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:08,796
What if I'm still hungry?

529
00:22:08,820 --> 00:22:09,916
Are you hungry?

530
00:22:09,940 --> 00:22:11,900
I...

531
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,820
I'm also hungry.

532
00:22:14,340 --> 00:22:16,476
Then how do you bear your hunger?

533
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:18,700
With all my might.

534
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:24,300
Little mister.

535
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:27,276
Aren't you the uncle who bought that magazine.

536
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,716
Yes, yes.

537
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:32,076
Little misters, have you seen my purse?

538
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:34,060
First of all, calm down.

539
00:23:34,260 --> 00:23:36,716
What does your purse look like?

540
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:37,836
It's brown.

541
00:23:37,860 --> 00:23:40,876
And filled with the Master's silver certificates.

542
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,860
You can stop looking.

543
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,756
Is this your purse?

544
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:48,716
That's exactly it.

545
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:49,836
I can't just give it to you.

546
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:51,676
I have to ask you a few questions.

547
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:53,516
Sure, as you should.

548
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,796
Go ahead and ask.

549
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:55,996
What do you have

550
00:23:56,020 --> 00:23:56,796
inside this purse?

551
00:23:56,820 --> 00:23:58,076
Six silver certificates.

552
00:23:58,100 --> 00:23:59,996
Five hundred and eighty-three silver dollars all together.

553
00:24:00,020 --> 00:24:01,996
It's a divident from the soap factory.

554
00:24:02,020 --> 00:24:02,796
Only silver certificates?

555
00:24:02,820 --> 00:24:04,076
Are there any silver coins?

556
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:05,836
Only certificates, no coins.

557
00:24:05,860 --> 00:24:07,916
Is there anything else besides that?

558
00:24:07,940 --> 00:24:09,036
There is also a bill

559
00:24:09,060 --> 00:24:10,556
with my name on it.

560
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:13,100
My name is Song Ah Di.

561
00:24:13,940 --> 00:24:17,420
What you've said all matches up. You can count it.

562
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:23,116
It's all here.

563
00:24:23,140 --> 00:24:24,796
Thank heavens.

564
00:24:24,820 --> 00:24:27,740
My master's money has finally been found.

565
00:24:28,420 --> 00:24:29,516
Thank you both.

566
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:30,100
Mister,

567
00:24:29,780 --> 00:24:30,956
you don't need to be like this.

568
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:32,476
Thank you both young gentlemen.

569
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:35,196
You've really saved this old man's life.

570
00:24:35,220 --> 00:24:36,396
I had thought that

571
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:38,156
if I couldn't find this money

572
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:39,996
I'd have to jump in the Huangpu river.

573
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:40,556
Don't be like this.

574
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:41,996
It's good enough that you got it back.

575
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:43,436
You're welcome.

576
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:44,636
Why don't you put it away,

577
00:24:44,660 --> 00:24:46,540
and get back home quickly.

578
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:47,836
Young gentlemen,

579
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:49,756
please go with me to see my master.

580
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:51,276
He will definitely reward you.

581
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:52,076
No, no.

582
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,836
It's nothing. There's no need for a reward.

583
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:55,036
You should go back home.

584
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:56,316
We have to go back to the school.

585
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:57,916
But, but.

586
00:24:57,940 --> 00:25:00,476
Young gentlemen,

587
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,916
let's see this to the end.

588
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:04,236
Look, it's already dark.

589
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:06,796
It's not safe for an old man

590
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:08,236
to be carrying so much money.

591
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:11,260
Would you two please escort me home?

592
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:15,500
Brother, let's see the uncle home.

593
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:19,900
Let's go.

594
00:25:21,380 --> 00:25:23,116
Don't worry. Let me give you a hand.

595
00:25:23,140 --> 00:25:24,540
This way.

596
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:30,756
Young gentlemen, you really are good people.

597
00:25:30,780 --> 00:25:32,260
{\an8}[Lu Wanliu residence, Shanghai]

598
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:34,556
This way, gentlemen.

599
00:25:34,580 --> 00:25:37,500
We're almost there.

600
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:40,316
Uncle Song.

601
00:25:40,340 --> 00:25:40,956
Let us help.

602
00:25:40,980 --> 00:25:41,436
No need.

603
00:25:41,460 --> 00:25:41,916
Uncle Song.

604
00:25:41,940 --> 00:25:44,236
You've got your own work.

605
00:25:44,260 --> 00:25:45,980
Here.

606
00:25:46,340 --> 00:25:47,596
We're here.

607
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:49,036
Please come in.

608
00:25:49,060 --> 00:25:50,860
Here, young gentlemen.

609
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,796
Please.

610
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:54,476
Right this way.

611
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:57,276
Uncle, now that the money has been safely delivered,

612
00:25:57,300 --> 00:25:58,716
we should be on our way.

613
00:25:58,740 --> 00:25:59,916
Not at all.

614
00:25:59,940 --> 00:26:01,276
Now that you're already here,

615
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:03,916
I would like to ask you two to help me testify.

616
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:06,156
Without you present, I can't explain it properly.

617
00:26:06,180 --> 00:26:07,996
Master will say I'm lying.

618
00:26:08,020 --> 00:26:08,796
Alright.

619
00:26:08,820 --> 00:26:11,356
Here, put it down.

620
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:13,420
You put it down too.

621
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,756
Here, take a seat.

622
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:16,956
A seat here. Alright.

623
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:18,796
Bring out the coffee.

624
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:20,476
Young gentlemen, please wait.

625
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:22,396
I will find the Master.

626
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:24,140
Please, sit.

627
00:26:24,260 --> 00:26:26,060
Master!

628
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:30,980
Please, the coffee.

629
00:26:30,980 --> 00:26:32,860
Thank you.

630
00:26:44,860 --> 00:26:45,916
I'm hungry.

631
00:26:45,940 --> 00:26:47,900
Bear it.

632
00:26:50,580 --> 00:26:52,700
I know.

633
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:55,820
Why are you two here?

634
00:26:55,820 --> 00:26:57,916
Why are you here?

635
00:26:57,940 --> 00:26:59,596
What do you mean, why?

636
00:26:59,620 --> 00:27:00,796
This is my home.

637
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:02,716
What are you two doing here?

638
00:27:02,740 --> 00:27:04,156
This is your home?

639
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:06,076
Mother, these are the two scoundrels from today

640
00:27:06,100 --> 00:27:06,980
I was telling you about.

641
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:08,636
Who's the scoundrel?

642
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,076
Can't you tell the truth for once?

643
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:11,916
Who spilled the water all over us today?

644
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:14,396
I did spill the water. Didn't I give you money?

645
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:15,756
Is that the way to give us money?

646
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:16,796
Then how should I have done it?

647
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:18,476
Fellow student, you have still not understood

648
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:20,316
how you are wrong, have you?

649
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:21,596
Who has wronged whom?

650
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:24,380
Setting up stalls without permission is in violation of school rules.

651
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:27,676
You've brought your wares here.

652
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:30,076
Were you going to set up a street stall in my home?

653
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:32,060
Set it up then.

654
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:35,276
Child, don't speak this way.

655
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:37,180
This way, Master.

656
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:41,036
Master, these are the two young gentlemen.

657
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:42,476
This is our Master.

658
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:44,316
How do you do?

659
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:46,556
How should address the two of you?

660
00:27:46,580 --> 00:27:48,396
I am Chen Qiaonian.

661
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:49,980
Chen Yannian.

662
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:51,916
Thank you both.

663
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:53,116
Thank you. You're welcome.

664
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:54,956
Dad, why are you thanking them?

665
00:27:54,980 --> 00:27:55,916
These are the two

666
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:57,756
who were arguing with me at school.

667
00:27:57,780 --> 00:27:59,756
They were setting up a stall to sell things.

668
00:27:59,780 --> 00:28:01,196
I kicked them out.

669
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:02,956
Sister, didn't we already explain to you

670
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:05,356
that our stall is a work-study program.

671
00:28:05,380 --> 00:28:06,876
You've already violated the school rules.

672
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:08,556
What work can you do? What student can you be?

673
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:09,836
Liu Mei!

674
00:28:09,860 --> 00:28:11,276
These are our guests!

675
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:13,516
How can you speak to guests in such a way?

676
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:15,500
How rude!

677
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:17,980
Please have a seat.

678
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,156
Alright.

679
00:28:22,180 --> 00:28:24,300
Sit, sit!

680
00:28:26,740 --> 00:28:28,396
Old Song has told me everything.

681
00:28:28,420 --> 00:28:30,316
The two of you, by not pocketing the money,

682
00:28:30,340 --> 00:28:32,476
have really helped our family.

683
00:28:32,500 --> 00:28:35,180
I must thank you properly.

684
00:28:35,860 --> 00:28:37,916
Old Song.

685
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:39,740
Master.

686
00:28:45,540 --> 00:28:48,236
This small gift is a token of my regard.

687
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:49,116
Please take it.

688
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:50,956
We can't take the money.

689
00:28:50,980 --> 00:28:52,476
We did what we ought to do.

690
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:54,236
If we really wanted money,

691
00:28:54,260 --> 00:28:56,156
couldn't we have gotten more with the five hundred?

692
00:28:56,180 --> 00:28:58,716
Now that the money has been safely returned,

693
00:28:58,740 --> 00:29:00,860
we are going to go now.

694
00:29:03,060 --> 00:29:04,796
Uncle, we will take our leave.

695
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:06,860
Wait, don't go.

696
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:08,156
The both of you,

697
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:10,220
stay, stay.

698
00:29:15,460 --> 00:29:16,716
I've heard you say

699
00:29:16,740 --> 00:29:19,036
that you are doing a work-study program.

700
00:29:19,060 --> 00:29:21,676
Then you must have some financial difficulties.

701
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:23,996
If you insist on refusing this money,

702
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:27,276
why don't we do this. I am the administrator at the school.

703
00:29:27,300 --> 00:29:29,036
I can waive all of your

704
00:29:29,060 --> 00:29:32,620
tuition and miscellaneous fees.

705
00:29:33,140 --> 00:29:35,356
It's a matter of course to pay for tuition if attending school.

706
00:29:35,380 --> 00:29:36,876
We pay what should be paid.

707
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,636
We'll figure it out ourselves.

708
00:29:38,660 --> 00:29:40,076
Thank you for your kindness.

709
00:29:40,100 --> 00:29:42,300
We will take our leave.

710
00:29:42,580 --> 00:29:45,300
Wen Yao!

711
00:29:45,060 --> 00:29:49,460
Wen Yao, is there anything to eat?

712
00:29:45,540 --> 00:29:47,276
I'm starving.

713
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:48,956
Yannian, Qiaonian?

714
00:29:48,980 --> 00:29:49,916
Uncle Wu?

715
00:29:49,940 --> 00:29:51,116
What are you doing here?

716
00:29:51,140 --> 00:29:53,900
Old Wu, do you know these two?

717
00:29:53,940 --> 00:29:55,196
Far more than know!

718
00:29:55,220 --> 00:29:57,276
These two are Chen Duxiu's sons.

719
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:59,036
Chen Yannian. Chen Qiaonian.

720
00:29:59,060 --> 00:30:01,916
So they are Chen Duxiu's young masters!

721
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:04,076
No wonder.

722
00:30:04,100 --> 00:30:05,196
Uncle,

723
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:06,876
he is his own person, and we are us.

724
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:08,876
We don't have anything to do with him.

725
00:30:08,900 --> 00:30:10,316
We're going back to school now.

726
00:30:10,340 --> 00:30:12,236
Any later and the school gate will be closed.

727
00:30:12,260 --> 00:30:14,300
Farewell.

728
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:17,100
Yes, alright.

729
00:30:18,820 --> 00:30:21,756
Take care, young gentlemen.

730
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:23,996
What? Just leaving like this?

731
00:30:24,020 --> 00:30:25,116
But, these two guys...

732
00:30:25,140 --> 00:30:27,180
How did they end up here with you?

733
00:30:27,220 --> 00:30:29,036
Elder Wu, have a seat.

734
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:30,156
Alright, alright.

735
00:30:30,180 --> 00:30:32,460
Get the cooks started on a meal.

736
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:36,140
{\an8}[Daheituo Village, Laoting, Hebei]

737
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:42,780
{\an8}[Li Baohua, son of Li Dazhao]

738
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:29,756
{\an8}[Li Xinghua, daughter of Li Dazhao]

739
00:31:29,780 --> 00:31:31,740
Xinghua.

740
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:34,940
Who are you?

741
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:38,876
You're acting like a real man now.

742
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:41,196
Mom!

743
00:31:41,220 --> 00:31:42,316
What is it?

744
00:31:42,340 --> 00:31:43,596
The weasels came again?

745
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:44,796
Grab a stick to drive them away!

746
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:46,076
Don't let them bite your younger sister again!

747
00:31:46,100 --> 00:31:48,365
It's not weasels!

748
00:31:48,389 --> 00:31:51,116
It's not weasels, then what is it?

749
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:53,586
A silly lump.

750
00:31:55,588 --> 00:31:56,703
{\an8}[Zhao Renlan, wife of Li Dazhao]

751
00:31:55,860 --> 00:31:59,501
Miss. The silly lump has come back.

752
00:32:04,043 --> 00:32:06,414
Came back...

753
00:32:07,380 --> 00:32:09,436
I thought you would only be able to come back at night.

754
00:32:09,460 --> 00:32:11,596
When I look at it, there is nothing wrong.

755
00:32:11,620 --> 00:32:13,756
I changed my to ticket to an early morning one.

756
00:32:13,780 --> 00:32:16,316
Rented a donkey cart. Getting on there's also no people.

757
00:32:16,340 --> 00:32:18,236
In no time, I was pulled to our house entrance.

758
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:20,300
Fast.

759
00:32:21,860 --> 00:32:23,436
The fire... firewood pile.

760
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:25,116
Those siberian weasels have been coming to the firewood pile.

761
00:32:25,140 --> 00:32:27,116
Xinghua, Xinghua's been bitten by them.

762
00:32:27,140 --> 00:32:28,556
Her, her brother grabs a stick

763
00:32:28,580 --> 00:32:29,756
driving away and hurrying over there

764
00:32:29,780 --> 00:32:31,820
to find weasels

765
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:33,676
Hurry, come here!

766
00:32:33,700 --> 00:32:34,556
This is your guys' dad!

767
00:32:34,580 --> 00:32:36,556
Don't you guys shout to want to find your dad all the time?

768
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:38,556
Hurry over, call for "dad".

769
00:32:38,580 --> 00:32:39,516
Dad's back.

770
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:40,918
Dad's come back. Quickly.

771
00:32:40,942 --> 00:32:42,176
Quickly.

772
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,286
Hurry to the front. Quickly go and call dad.

773
00:32:44,287 --> 00:32:46,286
Hurry, go!

774
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:55,740
Xinghua.

775
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:04,556
Dad!

776
00:33:04,580 --> 00:33:05,419
You...

777
00:33:05,443 --> 00:33:07,139
This child, all day who do you keep shouting at?

778
00:33:07,140 --> 00:33:07,916
Want you dad, want your dad. Go search.

779
00:33:07,940 --> 00:33:08,796
Dad's come, and you...

780
00:33:08,820 --> 00:33:10,476
You stay in your den.

781
00:33:10,500 --> 00:33:12,236
You quickly!

782
00:33:12,260 --> 00:33:13,116
Stop being stubborn there.

783
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:15,196
You, quickly go.

784
00:33:15,220 --> 00:33:17,260
Li Baohua

785
00:33:17,380 --> 00:33:19,660
Are you still wetting your bed right now?

786
00:33:23,620 --> 00:33:26,876
Xinghua, Xinghua, Xinghua!

787
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:27,596
Enough now, enough now.

788
00:33:27,620 --> 00:33:28,796
Come down, come down.

789
00:33:28,820 --> 00:33:30,396
Don't let your dad hold you.

790
00:33:30,420 --> 00:33:32,780
Dad's tired. Quickly.

791
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:34,156
Wash your face, wash your face.

792
00:33:34,180 --> 00:33:36,476
Dad's washing his face, is that okay?

793
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:37,196
Dad's going to wash his hands.

794
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:39,516
Then I'll hold you again, is that okay?

795
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:41,580
Good.

796
00:33:44,740 --> 00:33:47,676
Xinghua, catch a big chaffinch.

797
00:33:47,700 --> 00:33:48,476
Slaughter chicken!

798
00:33:48,500 --> 00:33:51,500
Tonight we're eating chicken!

799
00:34:06,580 --> 00:34:09,020
Slaughter chicken!

800
00:34:09,140 --> 00:34:17,020
Our... our family can finally eat a reunion meal.

801
00:34:18,340 --> 00:34:19,756
Student Li Baohua.

802
00:34:19,780 --> 00:34:22,860
Come out and catch chicken.

803
00:34:25,780 --> 00:34:27,116
Stop it over there!

804
00:34:27,140 --> 00:34:28,476
Let me help, miss.

805
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:30,380
No problem.

806
00:34:30,900 --> 00:34:33,436
Dad, what is this?

807
00:34:33,460 --> 00:34:36,220
This is called Junqi (land battle chess).

808
00:34:36,900 --> 00:34:39,916
Dad, why didn't buy me something good to eat?

809
00:34:39,940 --> 00:34:43,580
Didn't you eat all the big reed flowers, you still want to eat something good?

810
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:46,476
How much good food are you able to eat?

811
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:49,516
But this land battle chess, we can play with it for a long time.

812
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:50,876
Do you guys know?

813
00:34:50,900 --> 00:34:52,476
When dad was in Japan,

814
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:54,796
everyone relied on this to relieve boredom.

815
00:34:54,820 --> 00:34:58,156
Baohua, don't think that this land battle chess doesn't look good.

816
00:34:58,180 --> 00:35:01,356
This is what dad personally made for you.

817
00:35:01,380 --> 00:35:02,462
Dad will teach you, okay?

818
00:35:02,462 --> 00:35:04,182
Okay

819
00:35:05,140 --> 00:35:06,156
This Junqi

820
00:35:06,180 --> 00:35:08,316
needs to have two people to battle.

821
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:09,676
What's a victory?

822
00:35:09,700 --> 00:35:10,876
I take this piece,

823
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:13,116
occupy your military command center.

824
00:35:13,140 --> 00:35:14,156
This is a victory.

825
00:35:14,180 --> 00:35:16,316
You see these pieces on the chessboard,

826
00:35:16,340 --> 00:35:18,876
The biggest piece within these pieces is this one.

827
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:21,820
General.

828
00:35:22,180 --> 00:35:24,716
The last one is this one, landmine.

829
00:35:24,740 --> 00:35:26,636
Landmine, excluding the military engineer,

830
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:28,316
is afraid of no one.

831
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:31,100
Xinghua.

832
00:35:31,220 --> 00:35:31,916
It's burning hot.

833
00:35:31,940 --> 00:35:32,796
Do you understand?

834
00:35:32,820 --> 00:35:34,156
Understand.

835
00:35:34,180 --> 00:35:34,556
Come.

836
00:35:34,580 --> 00:35:35,676
I'll teach you how to move.

837
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:37,276
Dad, drink water.

838
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:39,980
Thank you, Xinghua!

839
00:35:40,420 --> 00:35:43,180
Dad, what is the biggest move?

840
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:46,076
Just now, didn't dad tell you?

841
00:35:46,100 --> 00:35:47,676
General.

842
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:51,676
Dad. Then when can you become the biggest official?

843
00:35:51,700 --> 00:35:53,916
Like this, then we can eat meat every day.

